# Token Optimisation (Cursor Sessions)

## Response Style

- No preamble ("Sure!", "Of course!", "Great question!").
- No trailing summary of what was just done — the diff is self-evident.
- Inline code for single identifiers; code blocks only when the user needs to copy.

## File Reading

- Read only the lines relevant to the task; request targeted ranges.
- Use symbol search before reading a whole file.
- After a large result, extract only the relevant portion before continuing.

## Edits

- Prefer targeted edits (Edit tool / inline diff) over full file rewrites.
- One concern per response; don't bundle unrelated changes.
